Measure definition: The percentage of males 21-75 years of age and females 40-75 years of age who were identified as having clinical atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease (ASCVD) and remained on a high or moderate-intensity statin at least 80% of the period.

Measure Name: Statin Therapy for Patients With Diabetes
Measure definition: The percentage of members 40-75 years of age with diabetes who do not have clinical atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease (ASCVD) and received at least one high or moderate-intensity statin.

Measure Name: Statin Therapy for Patients With Diabetes
Measure definition: The percentage of members 40-75 years of age with diabetes who do not have clinical atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease (ASCVD) and remained on a high or moderate-intensity statin at least 80% of the period.

Measure Name: Use of Spirometry Testing in the Assessment and Diagnosis of COPD
Measure definition: The percentage of adults 40 years of age and older with a new diagnosis of COPD or newly active COPD, who received spirometry testing to confirm the diagnosis.

Measure Name: Appropriate Treatment for Children With URI
Measure definition: The percentage of children 3 months-18 years of age who were given a diagnosis of URI and were not dispensed an antibiotic prescription.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had no well-child visits with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had one well-child visit with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had two well-child visits with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had three well-child visits with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had four well-child visits with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had five well-child visits with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the First 15 Months of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children who turned 15 months old and had at least six well-child visits with a primary care physician during their first 15 months of life.

Measure Name: Well-Child Visits in the Third, Fourth, Fifth and Sixth Years of Life
Measure definition: The percentage of children 3-6 years of age who received one or more well-child visits with a primary care practitioner .

Measure Name: Weight Assessment and Counseling for Nutrition and Physical Activity for Children/Adolescents
Measure definition: The percentage of children 3-17 years of age who had an outpatient visit with a primary care practitioner or OB/GYN and who had evidence of BMI percentile documentation.

Measure Name: Weight Assessment and Counseling for Nutrition and Physical Activity for Children/Adolescents
Measure definition: The percentage of children 3-17 years of age who had an outpatient visit with a primary care practitioner or OB/GYN and who had evidence of counseling for nutrition.
